Findings: CHEST, SINGLE SUPINE VIEW. ET tube tip is 52 cm above the carina, at the level of the lower medial clavicular heads. An NG tube is present --tip and side port over the stomach. No supine film evidence of pneumothorax and no gross effusion identified.
